        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 6:30PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 9 miles southwest of Bonners Ferry, moving north at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bonners Ferry, Moyie Springs, Copeland, Naples, Meadow Creek
Campground, and Meadow Creek.

This includes the following highways...
U.S. Highway 95 in Idaho between mile markers 495 and 536.
U.S. Highway 2 in Idaho between mile markers 65 and 80.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
